WEBVTT

00:06.006 --> 00:09.009
[soft piano music]

00:09.009 --> 00:16.016
♪ ♪

01:42.645 --> 01:44.271
[doorbell rings]

01:45.606 --> 01:47.107
[tapping]

01:50.402 --> 01:51.946
- Hey.
- Hey.

01:51.946 --> 01:54.281
- Wanna play shuffleboard?
- Sounds great.

01:54.281 --> 01:57.076
Hold on a second.
Let me get my outside shoes.

01:57.076 --> 01:58.828
So what have you
been doing today?

01:58.828 --> 02:00.704
Not too much. Had some
breakfast, did my stretching,

02:00.704 --> 02:02.373
got through almost
half a crossword,

02:02.373 --> 02:03.874
June left me...

02:03.874 --> 02:05.793
- Reorganized my shirts...
- Wait, what?

02:05.793 --> 02:07.837
June left you?
What...what do you mean?

02:07.837 --> 02:10.089
Well...she left.

02:10.089 --> 02:12.675
- Where did she go?
- She didn't say.

02:12.675 --> 02:15.052
- Is she coming back?
- I don't know.

02:15.052 --> 02:16.762
What the hell
are you talking about?

02:16.762 --> 02:18.472
I'm not sure what else
I can tell you.

02:18.472 --> 02:20.724
She was kinda vague
in the letter.

02:20.724 --> 02:23.394
There's a letter?
Can I see it?

02:23.394 --> 02:25.020
It's kinda private.

02:25.020 --> 02:27.147
Holy shit.

02:27.147 --> 02:30.276
You left out the best part:
she was lez the whole time.

02:30.276 --> 02:32.278
That's not exactly accurate.

02:32.278 --> 02:35.364
Dude, she dumped you for Kase...
who's a chick.

02:35.364 --> 02:37.575
It doesn't say anywhere
that she's dumping me.

02:37.575 --> 02:39.034
She just said that
she needs some more time

02:39.034 --> 02:40.494
to figure things out.

02:40.494 --> 02:42.162
She happens to be
going with Kase,

02:42.162 --> 02:44.248
maybe just as friends;
it's fine.

02:44.248 --> 02:45.791
It's fine?

02:45.791 --> 02:47.084
I can't believe you're not
freaking out right now.

02:47.084 --> 02:49.253
Well...I'm an adult, Mark.

02:49.253 --> 02:50.588
I can't do that stuff.

02:53.465 --> 02:55.259
Look, I know it must be hard.

02:55.259 --> 02:56.760
Would it make it easier for you
if we just kinda went through

02:56.760 --> 02:58.512
the things we didn't like
about her?

02:58.512 --> 03:00.472
- No.
- I'll start.

03:00.472 --> 03:02.433
She didn't laugh at my jokes.
Bad sense of humor.

03:02.433 --> 03:04.476
That's not true.
She was hilarious.

03:04.476 --> 03:05.769
Well, she was a poser.

03:05.769 --> 03:07.438
What does that even mean?

03:07.438 --> 03:09.857
She posed as a straight lady,
right?

03:09.857 --> 03:11.525
June isn't gay,

03:11.525 --> 03:14.069
not that those terms mean...

03:14.069 --> 03:16.447
They're just...[sighs]

03:16.447 --> 03:18.282
Sexuality,
it's not cut and dry.

03:18.282 --> 03:19.783
It's...

03:19.783 --> 03:22.870
it's a little bit like a...
a spectrum.

03:22.870 --> 03:25.873
What in the fuck
are you talking about?

03:25.873 --> 03:27.458
[sighs] Okay...

03:27.458 --> 03:29.501
I'm asking you as my friend,

03:29.501 --> 03:33.130
please, stop saying bad things
about my wife,

03:33.130 --> 03:35.341
who could be coming back
at any point.

03:35.341 --> 03:36.800
For your sake,
I hope that's true,

03:36.800 --> 03:40.054
but here's the thing:
Kase is hot as shit.

03:40.054 --> 03:42.097
I love her husky voice.

03:42.097 --> 03:44.600
Just thinking about it's
kinda giving me a boner.

03:44.600 --> 03:47.186
All right, let's just
stop talking about it

03:47.186 --> 03:49.772
and let's go play shuffleboard.

03:49.772 --> 03:52.149
[Kase] I can't believe
we're finally doing this.

03:52.149 --> 03:54.318
- I feel so good. [chuckles]
- I know.

03:54.318 --> 03:57.237
We've never been
this far out before.

03:57.237 --> 03:59.657
Hey, what do you think
Oceanside's gonna be like?

03:59.657 --> 04:02.159
I...I'm picturing,

04:02.159 --> 04:04.036
like, a castle on the beach

04:04.036 --> 04:05.955
and maybe some horses
to ride.

04:05.955 --> 04:08.123
And honestly...

04:08.123 --> 04:10.042
I wouldn't mind a Wendy's.

04:10.042 --> 04:12.211
Did you ever dip your
French fries in your Frosty?

04:12.211 --> 04:13.671
[scoffs] Of course I have.

04:13.671 --> 04:15.381
What do you take me for,
a fucking amateur?

04:15.381 --> 04:18.467
[laughs]

04:18.467 --> 04:20.469
Are you all right?

04:20.469 --> 04:22.346
You're not having
second thoughts, are you?

04:22.346 --> 04:24.390
Oh, I just...I'm...

04:24.390 --> 04:26.892
I'm worried about
how I left things with Oscar.

04:26.892 --> 04:29.228
I feel like I should've
talked to him in person.

04:29.228 --> 04:31.522
How many times have you
tried to talk to him,

04:31.522 --> 04:33.148
dead or alive?

04:33.148 --> 04:35.818
Have you ever gotten
anything out of it?

04:35.818 --> 04:37.945
[soft solemn music]

04:37.945 --> 04:39.321
Not really, no.

04:39.321 --> 04:41.699
He would've made you
feel guilty...

04:41.699 --> 04:43.367
♪ ♪

04:43.367 --> 04:46.745
Or maybe you would've talked
yourself out of coming.

04:46.745 --> 04:48.831
I feel like it's gonna be fine.

04:48.831 --> 04:50.499
You're just tired.

04:50.499 --> 04:52.918
I am a little tired.

04:52.918 --> 04:56.880
♪ ♪

04:59.591 --> 05:01.343
Ready to play, Mrs. Nakajima?

05:01.343 --> 05:04.179
Heard you're a big cheater,
so I wanna be on your team.

05:11.020 --> 05:12.938
You're a good man.

05:12.938 --> 05:14.398
Don't worry.

05:14.398 --> 05:17.776
You'll find someone else
and be happy.

05:17.776 --> 05:18.777
Thank you.

05:22.656 --> 05:25.075
How did Mrs. Nakajima know
about June leaving?

05:25.075 --> 05:26.577
Oh, I told her.

05:26.577 --> 05:29.038
Why? Why would you do that?

05:29.038 --> 05:31.165
Because...

05:31.165 --> 05:33.709
I really care about you?

05:33.709 --> 05:36.336
Come on, it's the first exciting
thing that's ever happened here.

05:36.336 --> 05:39.506
You were in the middle of
a fucked-up gay love triangle.

05:39.506 --> 05:41.800
Okay, moving forward,

05:41.800 --> 05:44.428
I'd like to keep it private,
do you understand that?

05:44.428 --> 05:46.513
I understand that,
but the problem is,

05:46.513 --> 05:48.724
it's hilarious.

05:48.724 --> 05:50.267
I'm sorry, that wasn't cool.

05:50.267 --> 05:52.061
- No.
- Let's just play.

05:52.061 --> 05:55.064
[enchanting music]

05:55.064 --> 06:02.071
♪ ♪

06:02.863 --> 06:05.407
I think this is it.

06:05.407 --> 06:07.659
Wow...

06:07.659 --> 06:10.662
[elegant music
playing faintly]

06:10.662 --> 06:17.211
♪ ♪

06:26.303 --> 06:28.180
[indistinct chatter]

06:31.975 --> 06:38.982
♪ ♪

06:55.958 --> 06:57.459
What do we do?

06:57.459 --> 07:00.003
I don't know, maybe
we should just get a drink.

07:00.003 --> 07:01.672
Okay.

07:01.672 --> 07:08.679
♪ ♪

07:10.889 --> 07:12.182
Oh...

07:12.182 --> 07:14.184
Oh, my God. [chuckles]

07:14.184 --> 07:16.603
- Cheers.
- Cheers to us.

07:16.603 --> 07:18.730
♪ ♪

07:18.730 --> 07:21.358
Oh, I'm sorry, were we not
supposed to take these?

07:21.358 --> 07:22.860
We...we'll put it back.
I'm sorry.

07:22.860 --> 07:24.778
No, it's fine.
Please, help yourself.

07:24.778 --> 07:26.280
That's what it's here for.

07:26.280 --> 07:29.158
I'm Kase,
and this is June.

07:29.158 --> 07:30.701
Hi. We're new here.

07:30.701 --> 07:33.328
We know.
We've been expecting you.

07:33.328 --> 07:35.622
- You have?
- Of course.

07:35.622 --> 07:37.374
Your first night here.

07:37.374 --> 07:40.836
I wish I could see
through your eyes right now.

07:40.836 --> 07:43.422
All possibilities are open.

07:43.422 --> 07:45.757
It's like being
a newborn child again.

07:45.757 --> 07:47.759
[Gregory chuckles]
You have to forgive Marisol.

07:47.759 --> 07:50.179
She tends to speak
a little poetically.

07:50.179 --> 07:52.181
Well, Gregory is so literal,

07:52.181 --> 07:54.433
I always know
exactly what he wants.

07:54.433 --> 07:55.851
It's exhausting.

07:55.851 --> 07:57.895
[laughter]

07:57.895 --> 07:59.438
Cool.

07:59.438 --> 08:01.106
It's, um...

08:01.106 --> 08:02.733
it's really pretty here.

08:02.733 --> 08:05.110
Well, thank you.
That's very kind.

08:05.110 --> 08:07.070
- Top off?
- Thank you.

08:07.070 --> 08:08.488
♪ ♪

08:08.488 --> 08:11.491
[stately music playing]

08:11.491 --> 08:15.704
♪ ♪

08:15.704 --> 08:17.372
[Gregory]
Wonderful to have you.

08:17.372 --> 08:20.209
We haven't had new visitors
in quite some time.

08:20.209 --> 08:21.919
Tell us a little bit
about yourselves.

08:21.919 --> 08:24.129
I was born and raised
in California.

08:24.129 --> 08:27.132
Um, went to school,
got a boring job,

08:27.132 --> 08:30.093
married to a guy who got into
brewing his own beer

08:30.093 --> 08:31.887
to avoid talking to me,

08:31.887 --> 08:34.014
and that about sums it up.

08:34.014 --> 08:36.183
Mm. June?

08:36.183 --> 08:38.143
♪ ♪

08:38.143 --> 08:39.603
I was an ER doctor.

08:39.603 --> 08:43.190
You know, pretty intense stuff.

08:43.190 --> 08:45.067
Ooh, the things I've seen.

08:46.276 --> 08:47.861
You don't have to do that.

08:48.987 --> 08:50.530
Do what?

08:50.530 --> 08:52.616
Tell us things
that aren't true.

08:52.616 --> 08:54.743
Oh, I was just joking around.

08:54.743 --> 08:57.913
[stammers] It's interesting,
both of you chose to tell us

08:57.913 --> 08:59.831
about what you did
when you were Currents.

08:59.831 --> 09:02.709
- I barely even remember.
- Neither do I.

09:02.709 --> 09:04.544
I think you'll find
the longer you stay here,

09:04.544 --> 09:07.089
the more your old life
will float away,

09:07.089 --> 09:09.007
almost like a...

09:09.007 --> 09:11.927
oh, how do you say it,
a...a dandelion.

09:11.927 --> 09:14.388
[chuckles]
She knows what a dandelion is.

09:14.388 --> 09:16.640
She just says that kinda stuff
for effect.

09:16.640 --> 09:18.934
I don't understand. Have you
guys just forgotten everything?

09:18.934 --> 09:20.727
Is that what happens?

09:20.727 --> 09:22.729
I see that that scares you
a little.

09:22.729 --> 09:25.274
It shouldn't.
Think of your life as a Current.

09:25.274 --> 09:27.901
What were the things you were
most often controlled by?

09:27.901 --> 09:31.154
- Fear? Anger? Guilt?
- Pornography?

09:31.154 --> 09:32.823
[Gregory] We don't have any
of those negativities here.

09:32.823 --> 09:34.616
We're beyond all that.

09:34.616 --> 09:36.451
It's quite freeing.

09:36.451 --> 09:38.161
Do you understand?

09:38.161 --> 09:39.871
Yeah.

09:39.871 --> 09:41.665
♪ ♪

09:41.665 --> 09:43.500
[Marisol whispering
indistinctly]

09:43.500 --> 09:47.754
♪ ♪

09:47.754 --> 09:50.841
- Is everything okay?
[Gregory] Yes, of course.

09:50.841 --> 09:52.676
If there's ever anything
that you need,

09:52.676 --> 09:54.761
don't hesitate to ask.

09:54.761 --> 09:56.471
Thank you.

09:56.471 --> 10:00.726
♪ ♪

10:00.726 --> 10:03.729
[reflective music]

10:03.729 --> 10:10.736
♪ ♪

10:12.696 --> 10:14.698
There you are.

10:14.698 --> 10:16.491
I made you some mochi.

10:16.491 --> 10:18.452
Mrs. Nakajima...

10:18.452 --> 10:19.786
you shouldn't have.

10:19.786 --> 10:21.580
Make sure you remember to eat.

10:21.580 --> 10:23.749
Depressed people never eat.

10:23.749 --> 10:26.668
Well, I'm not depressed,
but thank you.

10:26.668 --> 10:29.379
I hope my niece dies soon
so she can meet you.

10:29.379 --> 10:31.089
Oh, no.

10:31.089 --> 10:33.925
That's such a kind thought,
but really, I'm okay.

10:33.925 --> 10:36.178
She's a lawyer,
and she can cook.

10:36.178 --> 10:39.765
Not just Japanese food.
She makes great nachos.

10:39.765 --> 10:42.601
- You like nachos?
- Yeah.

10:42.601 --> 10:44.728
Everybody does.

10:46.104 --> 10:49.733
[pleasant music]

10:49.733 --> 10:52.736
[birds squawking]

10:52.736 --> 10:56.531
♪ ♪

10:56.531 --> 10:59.368
[Marisol speaking indistinctly]

10:59.368 --> 11:01.286
June and Kase!

11:01.286 --> 11:04.456
I think you are going
to really love this.

11:04.456 --> 11:06.208
We call them ocean stands.

11:06.208 --> 11:09.127
So we walk out past the waves,

11:09.127 --> 11:12.047
and we stand
on the bottom of the ocean.

11:12.047 --> 11:14.800
Yeah...I don't know,
I'm not much of a water person.

11:14.800 --> 11:18.345
Carl used to make us rent
Jet Skis all the time.

11:18.345 --> 11:19.638
So much Jimmy Buffett.

11:19.638 --> 11:21.098
- Ooh.
- Bad memories.

11:21.098 --> 11:24.226
That is why you should
let them go and join us.

11:24.226 --> 11:25.769
No, I think I'm gonna go back.

11:25.769 --> 11:27.479
We saw a breakfast buffet
on the way down,

11:27.479 --> 11:30.565
and I'm still regretting
passing it up.

11:30.565 --> 11:31.858
I'm sad to see you go,

11:31.858 --> 11:35.195
but I'm glad we had
this interaction.

11:35.195 --> 11:36.363
Sure.

11:36.363 --> 11:38.198
- Bye.
- Bye.

11:38.198 --> 11:41.201
I think you will find this
very peaceful.

11:41.201 --> 11:42.744
Let's go!

11:42.744 --> 11:45.080
[June] I'll give it a shot.

11:45.080 --> 11:47.457
I tried a meditation class
at the Y once,

11:47.457 --> 11:50.502
but all I could think about
was not farting.

11:50.502 --> 11:52.879
What a delightful story.

11:54.714 --> 11:57.551
[both gasp, laugh]

11:57.551 --> 11:59.886
[June] Whoo! Whoo-hoo!

11:59.886 --> 12:02.889
[atmospheric music]

12:02.889 --> 12:09.896
♪ ♪

12:24.077 --> 12:25.537
[knocking]

12:30.542 --> 12:32.711
- Oh, hey.
- Hey.

12:32.711 --> 12:34.671
Just coming by to see
how things were going.

12:34.671 --> 12:37.215
- Oh.
- What's up with your hands?

12:37.215 --> 12:40.135
Uh...very weird.
[chuckles]

12:40.135 --> 12:41.928
- They're covered in gray shit.
- Yeah, you're right.

12:41.928 --> 12:44.556
Uh, well, I should wash them.
I'm gonna do that now.

12:44.556 --> 12:46.266
What are you doing?

12:46.266 --> 12:48.059
Nothing.

12:48.059 --> 12:49.686
[sighs]

12:49.686 --> 12:51.563
Holy crap.

12:53.356 --> 12:56.193
- What?
- Dude, you have gone psycho.

12:56.193 --> 12:57.944
Psycho for crafting, maybe.

13:01.323 --> 13:04.826
Are you trying to...make her?

13:04.826 --> 13:07.120
I don't know exactly
where it's going,

13:07.120 --> 13:09.539
but...you know...

13:09.539 --> 13:11.541
creative process.

13:11.541 --> 13:13.251
This isn't good.

13:14.544 --> 13:15.879
You know what needs
to happen now?

13:15.879 --> 13:17.631
- We need to get you laid.
- No.

13:17.631 --> 13:19.925
What about, uh,
messed-up-teeth lady?

13:19.925 --> 13:22.093
She's crazy.
She'd be up for it.

13:22.093 --> 13:25.931
No, Mark, I'm not interested
in dating Caroline.

13:25.931 --> 13:27.891
She has a name, by the way.

13:27.891 --> 13:29.935
Okay, so what about Derek?

13:29.935 --> 13:31.394
Derek?

13:31.394 --> 13:32.729
What? What's so crazy
about that?

13:32.729 --> 13:34.689
You said in your era,
everyone was gay.

13:34.689 --> 13:36.608
No, not everyone.

13:36.608 --> 13:38.527
I mean, I guess...

13:38.527 --> 13:40.111
Well, maybe.

13:40.111 --> 13:43.323
Just...just forget
all of that, okay?

13:43.323 --> 13:46.117
I am not giving up on June.

13:46.117 --> 13:48.078
We built a life together
when we were alive.

13:48.078 --> 13:50.914
Then we built another life
together when we were dead.

13:50.914 --> 13:53.917
I...I've just invested a lot.

13:53.917 --> 13:55.460
Okay.

13:55.460 --> 13:57.754
So what are you gonna do?

13:57.754 --> 13:59.965
I guess...

13:59.965 --> 14:02.551
I have to go find her.

14:02.551 --> 14:04.386
Fine, do whatever you want.

14:05.220 --> 14:06.721
Wait.

14:06.721 --> 14:08.557
I still need your help.

14:08.557 --> 14:10.642
I don't know where she went.

14:10.642 --> 14:11.685
[sighs]

14:11.685 --> 14:15.021
This is gonna suck, but...

14:15.021 --> 14:18.608
I think I know someone
who might be able to help you.

14:18.608 --> 14:20.777
He's been here
longer than anybody.

14:20.777 --> 14:22.445
Who?

14:22.445 --> 14:25.407
[laid-back jazz music playing]

14:25.407 --> 14:27.284
My loves!

14:27.284 --> 14:29.160
Why don't you
come along with us?

14:29.160 --> 14:31.580
- Where are you going?
- Out to the road.

14:31.580 --> 14:36.376
♪ ♪

14:36.376 --> 14:39.379
[soft ambient music]

14:39.379 --> 14:40.839
♪ ♪

14:40.839 --> 14:44.634
[woman singing operatically]

14:44.634 --> 14:48.096
Hey, Josiah.
This is my friend Oscar.

14:48.096 --> 14:49.931
Hey there, little guy.

14:49.931 --> 14:54.311
♪ ♪

14:54.311 --> 14:57.230
We actually, um...
we wanna ask you something.

14:57.230 --> 14:59.274
But I'm playing with my train.

14:59.274 --> 15:00.900
Well, it's kind of important.

15:00.900 --> 15:03.361
You can play too.

15:03.361 --> 15:05.405
I'm good at sharing.

15:05.405 --> 15:12.412
♪ ♪

15:14.706 --> 15:16.416
The train is full of people,

15:16.416 --> 15:18.752
but where are they all going?

15:18.752 --> 15:20.795
I bet they're going to work.

15:20.795 --> 15:24.257
No, it's not that kinda train.

15:24.257 --> 15:25.925
What kind of a train is it?

15:25.925 --> 15:27.469
A choo-choo train.

15:27.469 --> 15:28.928
Choo-choo trains
can go to work.

15:28.928 --> 15:31.264
Stop being a weirdo.
This is important.

15:31.264 --> 15:32.515
You're funny, Mark,

15:32.515 --> 15:35.101
but inside, you're sad.

15:35.101 --> 15:36.561
[chuckles]
I kind of agree with that.

15:36.561 --> 15:38.772
It's something we should
explore further.

15:38.772 --> 15:41.858
But I really need your help.

15:41.858 --> 15:45.320
My wife, she left town with,
um, a special friend.

15:45.320 --> 15:47.280
[chuckles]
Is that what we're calling it?

15:47.280 --> 15:48.615
Yes.

15:48.615 --> 15:50.283
And...

15:50.283 --> 15:52.535
I need to find her.

15:52.535 --> 15:54.245
Where could she have gone?

15:54.245 --> 15:55.914
Look at the track.

15:55.914 --> 15:57.457
Look at where the train goes.

15:57.457 --> 16:00.043
We don't care about that.
We care about his wife.

16:00.043 --> 16:02.170
There's only two stops.

16:02.170 --> 16:03.755
♪ ♪

16:03.755 --> 16:06.174
Oh, maybe he's trying
to tell us something.

16:06.174 --> 16:08.343
Are you saying that there's...

16:08.343 --> 16:11.096
another stop,
another place we can go?

16:11.096 --> 16:12.472
Yeah...

16:12.472 --> 16:14.808
but it's so far away.

16:14.808 --> 16:16.267
What is it?

16:16.267 --> 16:19.062
Uh, you know...
what's it like there?

16:19.062 --> 16:20.855
Everyone there is like me.

